### **Tokamak Rollup Hub Infrastructure Upgrade and Staking V2 Progress**

# ![][image1]2025 Tokamak Network Bi-Weekly Report \#8 : 5/16 \~ 5/3

### Highlight

This week, our primary focus was on upgrading the Tokamak Rollup Hub (TRH) infrastructure and continuing the integration of Staking V2. We made notable progress in advanced chain configuration, internal audits for L1 contract verification, and preparing UI services for deployment.

The second round of testing for TRH SDKv1 was completed on May 20, marking a key step toward its community release.  
[**SDKv1**](https://www.notion.so/tokamak/SDK-Revised-guide-2-1e0d96a400a3806db1c3ec0cdbc4eeea) is Tokamak’s developer toolkit that enables projects to easily launch and manage their own appchains.  
[**Staking V2** **Integration**](https://www.notion.so/tokamak/Candidate-Registration-Contract-Verification-SDK-Testing-1fcd96a400a38030bd2bcd869e0816b7) allows these appchains to join the Tokamak DAO and earn rewards based on their [**Layer 2 network growth**](https://github.com/tokamak-network/papers/blob/master/cryptoeconomics/tokamak-cryptoeconomics-en.md#222-ton-staking-v2).

### Technology Development

#### 2.1. Tech Development

Tokamak Network is an On-demand Layer 2 Platform and strives to provide various Layer 2 protocols to its users.![][image4]

* There have been 447 commits in 47 repositories in the Tokamak Network GitHub during the past two weeks. Users can check the category and types of each commit in the following chart. The number of commitments by detailed theme is as follows, and detailed development progress can be found in [Tokamak Network GitHub](https://github.com/tokamak-network).

2.2 Developing a Sybil-Resistance System for Decentralized Applications ([Overview](https://tokamak.notion.site/03cc941223844f30ba4473e98b1275a7?pvs=25)).

* Successfully implemented batch builder functionality to process transactions and save them in the state database. Updated the synchronizer with transaction processor integration, enabling proper handling of deposit transactions. Enhanced API endpoints to fetch transactions by page and address, with improved sorting based on block number, timestamp, and gas fees. Fixed critical database initialization issues for both forger and synchronizer components.

2.3 Developing Zero-Knowledge Proof-Based On-Demand Rollups ([Overview](https://www.google.com/url?q=https://medium.com/tokamak-network/project-tokamak-zk-evm-67483656fd21&sa=D&source=docs&ust=1734490765043963&usg=AOvVaw0KzcrtZJnAnxzX0oQiIp8Q)).

* The frontend compilers of Tokamak zk-EVM have been highly optimized, which significantly reduces the execution time of backend algorithms.  
* The first version of our secure multi-party computation protocol for the setup of Tokamak zk-EVM has been implemented.  
* The first version of a Solidity verifier contract for Tokamak zk-EVM has been implemented.  
* We are developing an easy-to-use GUI for Tokamak zk-EVM, which will be released in June.

#### 2.4. Developing Decentralized Staking and Governance ([Overview](https://tokamak.notion.site/49e44e989c514bd683e077c01cc8f143?pvs=25)).

* Successfully implemented the DAO agenda metadata repository with comprehensive validation system, including transaction, event, and signature verification. Enhanced the DAO community version with improved agenda submission workflow, PR creation for metadata, and robust error handling. Updated the DAOCommittee contract with new versions (V2 and V3) that passed both Sepolia and Mainnet tests. Implemented critical fixes for the Simple Staking V2 interface, including calculator improvements and unstakable value calculation.

#### 2.5. Advancing Developer-Centric Appchain Infrastructure ([Overview](https://tokamak.notion.site/1433390669554ae5b09e400f4c9c0fd4?pvs=25)).

* The Distributed Random Number generator sub project significantly enhanced the Commit-Reveal2 system with optimized component rendering, proper memoization, and improved error handling. The Project also implemented a robust timeout handling mechanism with specific error messaging for DRPC timeout errors,Developed ConsumerExampleV2 contract with enhanced request information storage and refund functionality and created comprehensive dispute logic interaction scripts for handling failure scenarios and system resumption. The SDK team upgraded the external secrets component in the Thanos stack from v0.16.0 to v0.17.0 to address breaking changes.

### Community

3.1. FAQ

These are some of the FAQs from the community. Please check the section below.

* **What is the Tokamak Rollup Hub and why is it important?**

1. The **Tokamak Rollup Hub** (TRH) is an **on-demand Layer 2 infrastructure platform** designed to enable **seamless deployment** and **end-to-end lifecycle managemen**t of Appchains. It aims to serve as a comprehensive hub that not only showcases our research outputs but also offers **essential tools** for integration and smooth network operations by deployers. TRH supports various **modular rollup technologies** and **developer-friendly SDKs**. In this report, we would like to mention the successful completion of the **second round of testing for SDKv1**, marking significant progress toward a **community-ready release**.

* **Why do we need a Rollup Hub? Aren’t there already many Layer 2 solutions?**

1. The Tokamak Rollup Hub is more than just another **Layer 2 solution** — it’s a **flexible platform** that empowers developers to deploy **modular Layer 2 Appchains**, supporting various rollup types like **Optimistic and ZK Rollups**. It enables the integration of components such as bridges, explorers, cross-trade module, random number generator, fraud proofs, and data availability layers based on specific project needs, allowing for **fully customized rollup chains**. Deployed chains can be **self-managed** by deployers on their own AWS infrastructure (with support for more environments planned), removing the dependency on third-party RaaS providers.  
2. Instead of offering a one-size-fits-all rollup, Tokamak Rollup Hub provides the flexibility to **launch and manage your own rollup architecture** tailored to your application’s needs. In that sense, it’s not just a rollup — it’s a **platform for building rollups**.

* **How to contribute to the Tokamak Network?**

1. **Grant program**: create your own project and apply for [GranTON](https://www.notion.so/Tokamak-Network-Grant-Program-GranTON-f2384b458ea341a0987c7e73a909aa21?pvs=4)**.**  
2. **Full time**: [apply for a full-time position](https://recruit.wanted.co.kr/p/QVxQS0MVRm5HWEpb) with compensation and get paid in USDT/USDC in addition to the [TON](https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/tokamak-network) grant paid by GranTON projects.  
3. **Part time**: apply for a part-time position in GranTON projects to expect to receive [TON](https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/tokamak-network) (TOKAMAK) rewards. Please contact the [project leader (owner)](https://www.notion.so/Tokamak-Network-Onboarding-523bc627bd374326b5dfbec3d3b0a8e1?pvs=21) directly and discuss with them.

* **How can I contact you if I would like to collaborate with the Tokamak Network team?**

  Thank you for your interest in collaborating with the Tokamak Network team. We are open to various forms of collaboration that foster Tokamak Network ecosystem growth and value.

  To discuss a potential collaboration, please send a brief description of your proposal to hello@tokamak.network, and we will review it and respond as soon as possible.
